### WorkflowExecutionStarted

This is always the first [Event](/workflows#event) <span id="i-b79430ab-98a8-4f62-b91b-9c5b63a3fa88" class="clickable-i clickable-link-preview">ðŸ”—</span><div id="preview-modal-b79430ab-98a8-4f62-b91b-9c5b63a3fa88" class="preview-modal"><div class="modal-header"><div id="x-b79430ab-98a8-4f62-b91b-9c5b63a3fa88" class="clickable-x clickable-link-preview">x</div><b>Link preview</b></div><div class="preview-modal-title">What is an Event?</div><div class="preview-modal-description">Events are created by the Temporal Cluster in response to external occurrences and Commands generated by a Workflow Execution.</div><div class="preview-modal-tags"><span class="preview-modal-tag">term</span> <span class="preview-modal-tag">explanation</span></div></div> in a Workflow Execution Event History.
It indicates that the Cluster received a request to spawn the Workflow Execution.

### WorkflowExecutionCompleted

This indicates that the [Workflow Execution](/workflows#workflow-execution) has successfully completed. | schedule_to_close_timeout        | The amount of time that a caller will wait for Activity completion. Limits the amount of time that retries will be attempted for this Activity.          |
| schedule_to_start_timeout        | Limits the time that an Activity Task can stay in a Task Queue. This timeout cannot be retried.                                                          |
| start_to_close_timeout           | Maximum amount of execution time that an Activity is allowed after being picked up by a Worker. This timeout is retryable.                               |
| heartbeat_timeout                | Maximum amount of time allowed between successful Worker heartbeats.                                                                                     |
| workflow_task_completed_event_id | The Id of the [WorkflowTaskCompleted](#workflowtaskcompleted) that the Event was reported with.                                                          |
| retry_policy                     | The amount of retries as determined by the service's dynamic configuration. Retries will happen until `schedule_to_close_timeout` is reached.            |

### ActivityTaskStarted

This [Event](/workflows#event) <span id="i-5c63d922-5997-416e-b64a-c02ec623f785" class="clickable-i clickable-link-preview">ðŸ”—</span><div id="preview-modal-5c63d922-5997-416e-b64a-c02ec623f785" class="preview-modal"><div class="modal-header"><div id="x-5c63d922-5997-416e-b64a-c02ec623f785" class="clickable-x clickable-link-preview">x</div><b>Link preview</b></div><div class="preview-modal-title">What is an Event?</div><div class="preview-modal-description">Events are created by the Temporal Cluster in response to external occurrences and Commands generated by a Workflow Execution.</div><div class="preview-modal-tags"><span class="preview-modal-tag">term</span> <span class="preview-modal-tag">explanation</span></div></div> type indicates that an [Activity Task Execution](/workers#activity-task-execution) <span id="i-fa0db25b-2df7-4472-887d-f9d71868c6b5" class="clickable-i clickable-link-preview">ðŸ”—</span><div id="preview-modal-fa0db25b-2df7-4472-887d-f9d71868c6b5" class="preview-modal"><div class="modal-header"><div id="x-fa0db25b-2df7-4472-887d-f9d71868c6b5" class="clickable-x clickable-link-preview">x</div><b>Link preview</b></div><div class="preview-modal-title">What is an Activity Task Execution?</div><div class="preview-modal-description">An Activity Task Execution occurs when a Worker uses the context provided from the Activity Task and executes the Activity Definition.</div><div class="preview-modal-tags"><span class="preview-modal-tag">term</span> <span class="preview-modal-tag">explanation</span></div></div> was started.
The SDK Worker picked up the Activity Task and started processing the [Activity](/activities#) <span id="i-78d96610-fa82-4062-a3f6-70efef80ec12" class="clickable-i clickable-link-preview">ðŸ”—</span><div id="preview-modal-78d96610-fa82-4062-a3f6-70efef80ec12" class="preview-modal"><div class="modal-header"><div id="x-78d96610-fa82-4062-a3f6-70efef80ec12" class="clickable-x clickable-link-preview">x</div><b>Link preview</b></div><div class="preview-modal-title">What is an Activity?</div><div class="preview-modal-description">In day-to-day conversation, the term "Activity" denotes an Activity Type, Activity Definition, or Activity Execution.</div><div class="preview-modal-tags"><span class="preview-modal-tag">term</span> <span class="preview-modal-tag">explanation</span></div></div> invocation.
Note, however, that this Event is not written to History until the terminal Event (like [ActivityTaskCompleted](#activitytaskcompleted) <span id="i-09502a53-4a1e-4ad8-afae-d67b07b438f4" class="clickable-i clickable-link-preview">ðŸ”—</span><div id="preview-modal-09502a53-4a1e-4ad8-afae-d67b07b438f4" class="preview-modal"><div class="modal-header"><div id="x-09502a53-4a1e-4ad8-afae-d67b07b438f4" class="clickable-x clickable-link-preview">x</div><b>Link preview</b></div><div class="preview-modal-title">Events reference</div><div class="preview-modal-description">Events are created by the Temporal Cluster in response to external occurrences and Commands generated by a Workflow Execution.</div><div class="preview-modal-tags"><span class="preview-modal-tag">reference</span></div></div> or [ActivityTaskFailed](#activitytaskfailed) <span id="i-ccecf17b-e1d5-444b-befe-2bf920c428f4" class="clickable-i clickable-link-preview">ðŸ”—</span><div id="preview-modal-ccecf17b-e1d5-444b-befe-2bf920c428f4" class="preview-modal"><div class="modal-header"><div id="x-ccecf17b-e1d5-444b-befe-2bf920c428f4" class="clickable-x clickable-link-preview">x</div><b>Link preview</b></div><div class="preview-modal-title">Events reference</div><div class="preview-modal-description">Events are created by the Temporal Cluster in response to external occurrences and Commands generated by a Workflow Execution.</div><div class="preview-modal-tags"><span class="preview-modal-tag">reference</span></div></div>) occurs.

| accepted_request                     | The request input and metadata initially provided by the invoker of the Update and subsequently relayed by Temporal Server to the Worker for acceptance and execution. |
